# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.

# dependencies
/node_modules
package-lock.json
/.pnp
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions

# testing
/coverage

# next.js
/.next/
/out/

# production
/build

# misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)
.env*
!.env.example

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

.vercel

# refinery (A1 lab) — raw snapshots + per-stage JSON
.refinery-cache/

# firecrawl tool cache
.firecrawl/
# Guard: a path-flattening bug can dump a .firecrawl/ output as a literal
# root-level filename (e.g. Usersethandevbrain-platform.firecrawlfiverr-data2.json),
# escaping the .firecrawl/ ignore above. Catch that shape (seen 2026-05-31).
Users*firecrawl*.json

# awesome-claude-code-toolkit — third-party research clone, not our code
awesome-claude-code-toolkit/

# session-scoped build-context intake (gated by .claude/hooks/check-build-context.mjs)
.claude/build-context.md

# Serena MCP project memories (local, re-onboarded per-environment)
.serena/

# dlt secrets and pipeline state (never commit credentials)
/.dlt/
.dlt/secrets.toml
.dlt/.pipeline/

# Defensive glob — catches any secrets.toml anywhere in the tree
# (e.g. ingest/secrets.toml if a future dlt entry point writes outside .dlt/)
**/secrets.toml

# ephemeral Claude Code session state (tasks, notes, handoffs — not hooks/settings)
.claude/tasks/
.claude/notes/
.claude/handoffs/

# transient worktrees scaffolded by parallel-agent dispatch — never tracked
.claude/worktrees/

# Claude Code per-machine permission overrides (settings.json stays shared)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Claude Code internal scheduler lockfile — runtime-only, per-machine
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# JetBrains / PyCharm — per-machine project files. Wired 2026-06-08 so PyCharm can
# open this repo (Python ingest layer + Postgres/DuckDB console) WITHOUT ever
# committing machine-specific config (interpreter paths, run configs, indexes) that
# would break another checkout or fight the prettier/pre-commit hooks. VS Code +
# Claude Code stay the primary driver. Rationale + setup steps + the "when to
# actually adopt this" triggers: docs/superpowers/plans/2026-06-08-jetbrains-when-we-scale.md
.idea/
*.iml

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/

# personal_vault backups — strategic insights, never commit
.private/

# LittleBird review-drop directory — ephemeral artifacts from prior Sonnet
# sessions. Anything worth keeping gets promoted to docs/superpowers/plans/
# with a README; the rest stays out of the tree.
.tmp_lb_review/

# Ingest runtime logs (LeePA + future ingest pipelines)
ingest/*.log

# Scratch / throwaway scripts — never commit
refinery/__scratch__/
__scratch__/
# Chart-deflection proof-harness output (scripts/prove-chart-deflection.mts) — scratch, never commit
scripts/.prove-chart-*

# RLS prod-probe — connects to the prod DB with a HARDCODED password on line 4.
# Operator's local-only verification tool; one `git add .` away from leaking the
# prod credential, so it must never be tracked. (Wired 2026-06-10.)
scripts/_rls_probe.py

# External raw data dumps — Redfin, Zillow, etc. (large CSVs/TSVs, not repo artifacts)
data/

# Claude Design — local-only logo/color/chat-chart reference for Claude Code mobile.
# Never push to GitHub. Stays in-house.
docs/design-reference/

# docs/audits/ holds dated snapshot files (e.g. *-corridor-character-snapshot.md)
# that are committed as diff/restore baselines. If a future audit-style file
# carries interactive checkboxes or per-row notes, gitignore that specific
# pattern case-by-case rather than the whole directory.

# In-progress / uncertain plan docs — ignored until promoted or deleted
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-26-corridor-broker-narrative-promotion/

# Closing-disclosure "janitor" — proprietary. The CONCEPT may be referenced in
# committed specs (brain-url-spec-v1, v3-synthesis-spec) and that's fine; but the
# actual program, profiles, research caches, and any janitor-named artifact never
# ship. The broad glob catches any janitor-named file at any depth — code or data.
# (To keep a specific janitor-named file tracked later, add a `!path` negation.)
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-02-closing-disclosure-janitor-evidence-chain.md
*janitor*
scripts/reddit.mjs

# Superpowers plugin runtime data — ephemeral, auto-generated per session
.superpowers/

# Personal strategy / trading notes — never commit (personal, not platform code)
/_private/

# MarketBeat / Colliers PDF drop folder — PDFs are large and proprietary
# Only the .gitkeep sentinel is tracked; actual PDFs go in this folder locally
ingest/drops/marketbeat_pdf/*.pdf

# Dev server output logs (captured by run scripts, never commit)
dev-stdout.txt
dev-stderr.txt

# Path-flattened Windows temp files — same bug as the firecrawl guard above;
# a script that writes to %TEMP%\foo.sql ends up in the repo root as
# "C:Users...foo.sql" when cwd is the repo.
# Pattern covers "C：Users…foo.sql" — U+F03A fullwidth colon flattens the Windows
# %TEMP% path into a root-level filename with a non-ASCII colon variant.
*mhs_permits_inserts.sql

# Map build artifacts — large source files, regenerated by mapshaper from Census TIGER
public/maps/fl_zips.geojson

# Email style-gallery preview — regenerated build artifact (scripts/preview-style-gallery.mts).
# A frozen design snapshot lives at docs/design/email/. Ignore the live regenerated root copy.
/style-gallery-preview.html

# graphify generated output
graphify-out/

# Outreach campaign dry-run artifacts (rendered previews + run reports)
outreach-runs/

# cloud-secrets: ONLY the encrypted vault.enc is committed. The passphrase and any
# decrypted/plaintext key material must NEVER be committed.
cloud-secrets/.passphrase
cloud-secrets/*.key
